<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="308" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,654,1585]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,560,873,901]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
Description of 3 
<superScript attach="left" box="[390,405,873,887]" fontSize="6" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">rd</superScript>
instar larva.
</emphasis>
Size (based on 
<specimenCount box="[741,899,876,901]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" type="generic">17 specimens</specimenCount>
): BL 
<quantity box="[962,1078,876,901]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1179999999999999" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" unit="mm" value="11.18">11.18 mm</quantity>
; HL 
<quantity box="[1136,1236,876,901]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.63" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" unit="mm" value="2.63">2.63 mm</quantity>
(2.49–2.77), HW 
<quantity box="[151,251,912,937]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.17" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" unit="mm" value="3.17">3.17 mm</quantity>
(2.91–3.42), ML 
<quantity box="[451,551,912,937]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.06" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" unit="mm" value="3.06">3.06 mm</quantity>
(2.77–3.34), HW/HL 1.20, ML/HL 1.16. General colouring grey with a darker grey pattern, dorsal side with a median paler area, ventral side pale mottled with dark grey; head capsule brown with a darker anterior portion, ventral side of the head brown with a darker area on the mouthparts and with a pair of distinctive longitudinal pale stripes (
<figureCitation box="[604,701,1020,1045]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[241,1334,212,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-51@22.[225,1361,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Libelloides longicornis (Linnaeus, 1764), 3rd instar larva (France: Var, Mt. Aurelien). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–c: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915215/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Fig. 12c</figureCitation>
), mandibles dark brown; legs with dark brown coxae and paler femora, tibiae and tarsi; setae of the body black. Head wider than long, noticeably dilated posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1323,1423,1056,1081]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[241,1334,212,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-51@22.[225,1361,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Libelloides longicornis (Linnaeus, 1764), 3rd instar larva (France: Var, Mt. Aurelien). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–c: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915215/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Fig. 12b</figureCitation>
); mandibles longer than the head capsule (
<figureCitation box="[618,716,1092,1117]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="22.[151,249,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[241,1334,212,1922]" captionTargetId="figure-51@22.[225,1361,193,1932]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 12. Libelloides longicornis (Linnaeus, 1764), 3rd instar larva (France: Var, Mt. Aurelien). Dorsal (above), ventral (middle) and lateral (below) view; a–c: diagnostic characters, see species description." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4915215" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4915215/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Fig. 12a</figureCitation>
); interdental pseudo-teeth: (3–4)(1–3)(0–1); external margin of the mandible with short setae. Pronotum pale brown with indistinct brown stripes; mesothoracic spiracles ochre with a black apex. Abdominal spiracles dark brown; VIII abdominal sternite pale with the exception of the odontoid processes; IX sternite pale with a dark apex.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,654,1585]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,343,1236,1261]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Bio-ecology.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1764" box="[353,513,1236,1261]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis box="[353,513,1236,1261]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">L. longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a common and euryoecious species occurring in open environments such as: grasslands, pastures, glades and scrublands. In 
<collectingCountry box="[674,726,1272,1297]" name="Italy" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Italy</collectingCountry>
this ascalaphid is mainly associated with mountainous biotopes and reports from lowlands are mainly attributable to stranded individuals (
<bibRefCitation author="Pantaleoni, R. A." box="[1025,1228,1308,1333]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" pagination="69 - 122" refId="ref16974" refString="Pantaleoni, R. A. (1990 a) I Neurotteri (Neuropteroidea) della Valle del Bidente-Ronco (Appennino Romagnolo). Bollettino dell'Istituto di Entomologia &quot; Guido Grandi &quot; dell'Universita di Bologna, 44, 69 - 122." type="journal article" year="1990">
Pantaleoni 1990 
<bibRefCitation author="Pantaleoni, R. A." box="[1215,1228,1308,1333]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" pagination="123 - 134" refId="ref17016" refString="Pantaleoni, R. A. (1990 b) Neurotteri e fasce di vegetazione in Romagna. Bollettino dell'Istituto di Entomologia &quot; Guido Grandi &quot; dell'Universita di Bologna, 44, 123 - 134." type="journal article" year="1990">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, 1990b), while in southern 
<collectingCountry box="[260,336,1345,1368]" name="France" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">France</collectingCountry>
this species shows a remarkably wider altitudinal range and it is common in Mediterranean environments (
<bibRefCitation author="Puissegur, C." box="[318,495,1380,1405]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" pagination="103 - 158" refId="ref17279" refString="Puissegur, C. (1967) Contribution zoogeographique, anatomique et biologique a la connaissance de sept especes et d'un hybride interspecifique d' Ascalaphus F. (Planip. Ascalaphidae). Vie et Milieu, 18, 103 - 158." type="journal article" year="1967">Puisségur 1967</bibRefCitation>
; Badano pers. obs.). The larvae are ambush predators living on the soil surface.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
