<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="308" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="21.[151,1437,654,1585]" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1452,1477]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The larvae of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1764" box="[483,642,1452,1477]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis box="[483,642,1452,1477]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">L. longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily recognizable, with the exception of the Sicilian endemic 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Angelini" baseAuthorityYear="1827" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siculus">L. siculus</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
thanks to the presence of longitudinal pale stripes running on the ventral side of the head. However 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1764" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">L. longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Angelini" baseAuthorityYear="1827" box="[347,461,1524,1549]" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="siculus">
<emphasis box="[347,461,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">L. siculus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are easily set apart for the different body colouring, besides the presence of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1764" class="Insecta" family="Ascalaphidae" genus="Libelloides" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neuroptera" pageId="21" pageNumber="308" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longicornis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">L. longicornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<collectingRegion box="[314,379,1560,1585]" country="Italy" name="Sicilia" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">Sicily</collectingRegion>
is unproven and unlikely ([Bernardi] Iori 
<emphasis box="[851,908,1560,1585]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="308">et al.</emphasis>
1995).
</paragraph>
